                    },
                    "company": "FMO - Dutch entrepreneurial development bank",
                    "description": "As Legal Counsel in the FMO Special Operations, Energy and Agriculture Team, I focus on debt and direct equity investments in the energy sector - my portfolio includes under-developed markets around the globe. Many of the investments we make are first-in-kind market leaders in their respective countries and require innovative legal approaches. In my role as Legal Counsel, it is my role to be \u201cmore than lawyer\u201d, managing not only the legal workstream but providing a key risk management and negotiating role as well. When FMO is lead arranged, it is my role to integrate the perspectives of multiple syndicate partners (including DFIs, funds and private commercial banks) and represent our partners in negotiations. In addition to transaction work, I provide in-house training, spearhead an initiative to improve cooperation between legal and commercial teams, and am always developing new approaches to project documentation. \n\nFMO, the Dutch Development Bank, has been investing in the private sector in developing economics for almost 50 years. Its mission is to empower entrepreneurs to build a better world. With an investment portfolio of EUR 10 billion spanning over 85 countries in the infrastructure, manufacturing and services sectors, FMO is one of the larger and more innovative bilateral private sector development banks globally",
                    "title": "Legal Counsel",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
